# MakaOS gcc specs override.
#
# The cross-toolchain ships default specs that are wrong for shared
# library builds:
#   *startfile: crt0.o%s            (unconditional — breaks .so)
#   *lib:       %{!shared: -lc }    (no libc for shared — breaks .so)
#
# For .so builds: skip crt0 (no _entry is needed) but still link libc
# so that strlen/malloc/etc. resolve.  For executables: unchanged.

*startfile:
%{!shared: crt0.o%s}

*lib:
-lc

